<section xml:id="strings_vocabulary"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Vocabulary</title>
  <p>
    <dl>
      <li>
        <title>character:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>character</h>
          </idx> A single letter, digit, punctuation mark, or other symbol
          in a string.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>char:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>char</h>
          </idx> The C++ data type for a single character.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>string:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>string</h>
          </idx> A sequence of characters; the primary data type for text.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>object</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>object</h>
          </idx> A code entity that bundles data and functions that operate on that data.</p> 
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>index:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>index</h>
          </idx> An integer variable or value used to indicate a character
          in a string.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>ASCII:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>ASCII</h>
          </idx> A character encoding standard that uses 7 or 8 bits to represent
          characters, allowing for 128 or 256 unique symbols.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>Unicode:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>Unicode</h>
          </idx> An international standard for representing characters in
          most of the world's languages.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>empty string:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>empty string</h>
          </idx> The string <pf>""</pf>, which contains no characters and
          has a length of zero.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>enhanced (range-based) for loop:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>enhanced for loop</h>
            <h>range-based for loop</h>
          </idx> An alternative syntax for traversing the
          characters of a string (or the elements of other collections).</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>escape sequence:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>escape sequence</h>
          </idx> A sequence of characters that represents a special character
          in a string, such as newline (<pf>\n</pf>) or tab (<pf>\t</pf>).</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>newline:</title>
        <p>
          <idx>
            <h>newline</h>
          </idx> A special character signifying the end of a line of text. Also known as <q>line ending</q>, <q>end of
          line</q> (EOL), or <q>line break</q>.</p>
      </li>
    </dl>
  </p>
</section>